Description: Comparatively wide net-sinker made of light grey schist, roughly oval in section, one slightly rounded end, one tapered end due to the natural shape of the stone. Two grooves incised at the ends, another short cut parallel to one of the grooves. The surface is uneven and rough, one side is covered in a thick salt crust.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D14.16.5, over upper floor
